parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Theta II engine can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. In some cases, it can also lead to engine fires.
symptoms: The engine makes a knocking or ticking sound
the check engine light is illuminated
the vehicle loses power or stalls
the engine shakes or vibrates
metal shavings are found in the oil
the vehicle is unable to start.

symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor

the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine or electrical system can cause a fire in the engine compartment, leading to accidents or injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the airbag system can lead to injuries or fatalities in the event of a crash, as the airbags may not deploy or may deploy incorrectly.

injuries or fatalities in crashes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the clock spring can cause the airbag light to come on and may prevent the airbags from deploying in the event of a crash.

clock spring failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the electrical system can cause the airbag light to come on, and may lead to other electrical issues, such as a burning smell or melted plastic.

electrical burning smell
melted plastic.

failure to repair recalled vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of vehicle safety systems, such as the seatbelt, can lead to injuries or fatalities in the event of a crash.

injuries or fatalities in crashes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of recall repair parts can lead to delayed or incomplete repairs, potentially causing safety risks and inconveniencing vehicle owners.
